headers.subject: [tosdr:2435] Skype keeps your messages for between 30-90 days

html:
Depending on the message type, messages are generally stored by Skype for a maximum of between 30 and 90 days unless otherwise permitted or required by law.

http://www.skype.com/en/legal/tou/

Title: Skype keeps your messages up to 90 days

Topic: track

Summary: Skype keeps your messages (video, instant messages, voice mail) for at least 30, but up to 90 days, claiming that this storage helps them facilitate message delivery when a user is offline and to help sync messages between devices, such as your computer and mobile phone.

Score: 35 (mediocre)

--
